  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Primary objective: Evaluate the prevalence of personality disorders in patients starting
      treatment for hepatitis C in the prison and determine their influence on the evolution of the
      disease.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Secondary objectives:

        -  Describe the management of patients with personality disorders on treatment for
           hepatitis C in the prison.

        -  Describe the characteristics of patients who discontinue the treatment and the reasons
           for stratifying by the presence of personality disorders.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
